pstree : process tree, startign from systemd

sudo systemctl --type=service --state=running: List running services
sudo systemctl status sshd : Look at one service in detail

sudo systemctl stop sshd : Stop a service (stop/start/restart)
sudo systemctl enable nginx : start the service after reboot
sudo systemctl disable nginx : stop the service on reboot

sudo journalctl -u nginx : logs of a service


----WRITE A CUSTOM SERVICE----

- Write a .sh script in /usr/local/bin

Example:
#!/bin/bash
echo "hello-punks"
sleep 5

- permissions: chmod 755 script.sh
-rwxr-xr-x 1 soi soi 39 Dec 15 15:08 script.sh
- write the service file in /etc/systemd/system as script.service

Example: 

[Unit]
Description=My Service
After=network.target

[Service]
User=soi
ExecStart=/bin/bash /usr/local/bin/script.sh
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

- ls -l script.service : -rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 167 Dec 15 15:16 script.service
- file permissions : chmod 755 script.service

- After this close the file, and reload the system daemon

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl start script
sudo systemctl status script
sudo journalctl -u script -f 

